{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"30c51fce-34cc-4576-af67-2bd0c17a8e49","content":"No pipeline files found in the repo, so here's a general migration guide:\n\n## Migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### 1. Update your test project\n\nAdd the MSTest runner and extensions to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n\n<ItemGroup>\n  <!-- TRX report support -->\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n  <!-- Code coverage -->\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"17.*\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n### 2. Replace VSTest@3 with `dotnet test`\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --\n      --report-trx\n      --coverage\n      --coverage-output-format cobertura\n```\n\n### 3. Publish results & coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish TRX results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '**/*.trx'\n    searchFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console.exe` | Built into the test binary |\n| Invocation | `VSTest@3` task | `dotnet test` / `DotNetCoreCLI@2` |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--report-trx` flag + NuGet package |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--coverage` flag + NuGet package |\n\nThe `--report-trx` and `--coverage` flags are passed after `--` because they're consumed by the test platform runner, not by `dotnet test` itself.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1ec611d7-1c69-43b8-b2f6-f22a622e25a5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no pipeline files in the repository. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps CI pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":740,"requestId":"E3DC:3835CB:1677543:1914854:6A052003"},"id":"f776cfc9-50b8-4f4a-b78a-02874c405cc0","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:06:24.637Z","parentId":"27040489-b9a2-4676-852a-c999b6e9fa14"}
